<HEADLINE> HK Stock, Futures Exchanges to Prolong Trading Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Both the Hong Kong Stock
Exchange and the Hong Kong Futures Exchange will prolong their
trading hours by five minutes starting from February 2, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Their closing time will be extended from 3:55 p.m. to 4:00
p.m., both exchanges announced here Friday.
</P>
<P>
"The extension of trading hours for stock futures will preserve
the symmetry between the trading hours of stocks on the Stock
Exchange of Hong Kong (STHK) and the corresponding stock future
contracts at the Hong Kong Futures Exchange (HKFE)," said Randy
Gilmore, chief executive of the HKFE Friday.
</P>
<P>
First introduced at HKFE on March 31, stock futures now cover
15 stocks. At present, both the futures exchange and stock
exchange conduct their trading from 10:00 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. and
from 2:30 p.m. to 3:55 p.m.. 
</P>
</TEXT>
