<HEADLINE> Nine Arrested in N.Ireland for Questioning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Nine people were arrested by
Northern Irish police on Friday for alleged involvement in recent
killings in the British divided province.
</P>
<P>
Six people detained in south Belfast and the other three were
being questioned about a murder attempt on a Roman Catholic man
who was seriously wounded as he left work in north Belfast on
Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
Eight men, six Catholic Romans and two loyalist Protestants,
have been killed in an upsurge of sectarian revenge attacks since
an extremist Protestant guerrilla group leader was gunned down on
December 27 in the Maze prison in Belfast.
</P>
<P>
The widespread killings have since plunged the fragile Northern
Ireland peace process into crisis.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, local reports said a "significant" quantity of
explosives were found at a house in loyalist Shankill Road in
south Belfast. A man was arrested for the storage of the
explosives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
