<HEADLINE> Big Rise in Passengers for Lufthansa in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The German airline Lufthansa
Friday said in Frankfurt that the group carried a record 44.5
million passengers in 1997, up 7.4 percent from the year before.
</P>
<P>
Excluding its subsidiary companies, Lufthansa itself carried
33.3 million passengers, an increase of 5.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to the company, it raised capacity utilization by 3.2
percent to a record high of 73.5 percent, and flights by 6.8
percent to 635.468.  
</P>
