<HEADLINE> Riot Leader Under Detention in Harare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Leader of Harare Office of the
International Socialist Organization (ISO) Munyaradzai Gwisai has
been detained at Avondale Police Station here by Zimbabwe's
Criminal Investigations Department (CID).
</P>
<P>
Assistant Inspector in charge of crime at the police station
Officer Chitimbe confirmed today that Gwisai was detained at
the station Thursday on allegations of inciting public
violence against the law and order maintenance act.
</P>
<P>
It is understood the charges of inciting public violence arose
from the recent food riots. The ISO claimed to be behind the
three-day food riots which rocked Harare, Chitungwiza and some
small towns.
</P>
<P>
The organization circulated fax messages exhorting the masses
to sustain the food riots which started on Monday for the whole
week.
</P>
<P>
The riots involved looting, stoning and burning of property
particularly at shopping centers in the high density suburbs.
</P>
</TEXT>
