<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4 Injured in Explosion in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 23 (Xinhua) -- At least four people were
injured in an explosion Friday morning in Karaj, a town on the
western outskirts of the capital, the official news agency IRNA
reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that an explosive device went off in the Sadar
area of Karaj when the International Qods (Jerusalem) Day rally
was passing.
</P>
<P>
A few cars parked nearby were damaged in the blast, IRNA said,
adding the explosion had no connection with the rally.
</P>
<P>
No further details is available.
</P>
<P>
Iranian people throughout the country held rallies Friday
morning to mark the International Qods Day set by Iran's late
spiritual leader Ayatollah Musavi Khomeini.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators voiced support for the Palestinian and Arab
struggle against Israeli occupation of Arab lands, particularly
Jerusalem, a holy city for Muslims, Jews and Christians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
