<HEADLINE> UN Chief to Visit Three European Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 23 (Xinhua) -- UN Secretary-General
Kofi Annan will be departing on January 26 on a trip to Paris,
London and Davos, Switzerland, the Office of the Spokesman for the
Secretary-General announced today.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, the Secretary-General will hold meetings with French
President, the Prime Minister, the Foreign Minister and the
President of the Senate.
</P>
<P>
In London, he will meet with Mr. Robin Cook, in his capacity as
Foreign Secretary of the United kingdom and as Chairman of the
Council of Minister of the European Union.
</P>
<P>
In Davos, the UN chief will attend the World Economic Forum. He
will attend various sessions of the Forum dealing with global
governance issues. He will also attend meetings with business
leaders with a view to enhancing cooperation between the United
Nations and the world business community. He will hold bilateral
meetings and consultations with several Heads of States and
Government who are also attending the World Economic Forum.
</P>
<P>
The Secretary-General is expected to be back in New York on
February 2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
