<HEADLINE> Landslide Deaths Increase to 63 in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The death toll caused by the
landslide in Chirongue District, Milange County in central
Mozambique has increased to 63, the Mozambique Information Agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The number of missing people has reached 78, who are believed
to have been buried under the ruined houses, and eight others
injured have been hospitalized, the report quoted the latest
statistics as saying.
</P>
<P>
The landslide has also destroyed 200 houses and one bridge in
the county town, leaving about 7,500 people homeless.
</P>
<P>
Virgilio Pinto Novo, head of Milange County, said that the
landslide casualties are likely to increase further.
</P>
<P>
The landslide was caused by heavy rains in northern and
central Mozambique since last Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
