<HEADLINE> China Urges to Respect Iraq's Dignity and Sovereignty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 23 (Xinhua) -- As a sovereign state,
Iraq's dignity and legitimate security concerns should be taken
into due consideration, Chinese Permanent Representative to the
United Nations Qin Huasun stressed here today.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Qin made the remarks after Richard Butler, the
Executive Chairman of the United Nations Special Commission
(UNSCOM) in charge of dismantling Iraq's weapons of mass
destruction, briefed the Security Council on his latest visit to
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
"We always believe that Iraq should fully implement the
relevant resolutions of the Security Council and cooperate with
UNSCOM so that the Special Commission could implement its mandate
entrusted by the Security council as early as possible," Qin said.
</P>
<P>
"At the same time as a sovereign state, Iraqi's dignity and
legitimate security concerns should be taken into due
consideration," Qin stressed.
</P>
<P>
"We attach great importance to the forthcoming technical
evaluation meetings. It is our hope that all parties concerned
will take a serious attitude towards these meetings and
prejudgement of these results are irresponsible and should be
avoided so that the experts will be able to make an objective
evaluation on Iraq's progress in implementing UN resolutions," he
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
