<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Construct 4 Irrigation Dams </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria is to spend 4.2 billion
Naira (about 50 million U.S. Dollars) on the construction of four
earth dams in the northern state of Kaduna, the News Agency of
Nigeria reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Alhaji Hamza Sakwa, Minister of the Federal
Ministry of Water Resources and Rural Development as saying that
the project will be executed under the 1998 budget and the 2000
rolling plan.
</P>
<P>
The project, when finished, will be able to provide water for
the irrigation of about 27,000 hectares of farmland, the minister
said during a recent visit to the state. 
