<HEADLINE> Chernomyrdin Has Talks with Kohl in Riga </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin had tete-a-tete talks in Riga with German Federal
Chancellor Helmut Kohl Thursday night on economic problems, the
Itar-Tass news agency reported Friday from Riga, Latvia.
</P>
<P>
Both the leaders are staying in Latvia to attend the second
meeting of the Council of Baltic Sea States (CBSS), which ended on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting they focused on the Russian cooperation with the
European Union and the existent limits on the Russian goods access
to Western markets.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin expressed hope that the EU commission will
recognize Russia as a country with the market economy at its
meeting of January 26, and that will enable Russia to become a
member of the World Trade Organization quicker.
</P>
<P>
The Russian premier said "Germany is our leading partner in
Europe. It is a partner that has been working on our market for
long and is carrying out major projects in Russia."
</P>
<P>
On the recently signed U.S.- Baltic Partnership Charter
Chernomyrdin said "it is the business of the Baltic countries what
and with whom to sign (accords)".
</P>
<P>
He meanwhile mentioned that the three Baltic states refused to
accept the Russian security guarantee proposal, saying Russia will
continue working in that direction and the proposal "remains
valid". 
</P>
</TEXT>
