<HEADLINE> Fiat to Expand Car Production in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Italian car manufacturer
Fiat Auto S.P.A. said Friday it would invest more than 250
million Rand (50 million U.S. Dollars) in the production of Fiat
cars in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a media briefing here, Fiat Auto S.P.A. president
and chief executive Roberto Testore expressed confidence that his
company was going to hold its own in a market be-deviled by a
subdued performance.
</P>
<P>
Fiat sold 8,000 units in 1997 and a similar performance was
expected this year.
</P>
<P>
Fiat Uno is the group's best known model in South Africa at
present.
</P>
<P>
The group also manufactures Iveco commercial vehicles and the
new Holland tractors which take up more than 40 percent of the
market share in the tractor business.
</P>
<P>
"We will spend most of 1998 preparing for the launch of the
Fiat Palio and the Alfa 156. I have the confidence that the car
will do well judging by the reception we got on the other Fiat
models," Testore said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
