<BODY>
<HEADLINE> W. Bank to Send Special Mission to Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 23 (Xinhua) -- World Bank President James
Wolfenshon said Friday he would send a special mission to kenya
to assess the destruction caused by the El Nino rains for
possible assistance.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks in Kampala, Uganda, when he paid a
courtesy call to President Daniel arap Moi who is on a two-day
official visit to Uganda, the Kenya News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank president once again took the opportunity to
congratulate President Moi on his re-election and inauguration as
Kenyan head of state.
</P>
<P>
On Moi's re-election, Wolfenshon has sent a congratulatory
message to the kenyan president, saying that the World Bank would
stand ready to support him and his government in his effort to
secure Kenya's leadership in the east African region.
</P>
<P>
The message said it was encouraging that President Moi issued
a strong message during his inaugural speech concerning his
determination to improve the well-being of the Kenyan people and
to address inefficiency in the government and corruption.
</P>
<P>
Wolfenshon noted that the World Bank would particularly be
committed to working with Kenya's government in improving the
management of public resources and maximizing their impact on
poverty reduction.
</P>
<P>
President Moi left here this morning for Kampala to attend the
Regional Leaders' Forum of Heads of State and Government and the
World Bank President. 
</P>
</TEXT>
