<HEADLINE> 7 Die in Avalanche in Alpes Mountains in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed and six
missing in an avalanche which came down on 32 people, including 26
children, Friday in Orres in the Alpes mountains in eastern
France, local television and press media reported.
</P>
<P>
Rescuers found 26 people by 18:00 local time (17:00 GMT),
including the seven dead, and are looking for the six still
missing, the reports quoted the prefectural government of
Hautes-Alpes as saying.
</P>
<P>
A group of 40 people left for the mountains in the daytime on a
sport class, but eight of them lost the group and thus escaped the
avalanche, said Agence France-Presse.
</P>
<P>
French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin immediately decided to go
to the scene of the avalanche Friday evening, after he learned
with great sadness about the accident, AFP quoted the entourage of
the prime minister as saying. 
