<HEADLINE> Qatar's Economy Records Dynamic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Qatar's gross domestic
product in 1997 was estimated to grow by 15.5 percent to reach
some 10.8 billion U.S. dollars, compared with 9.1 billion dollars
in 1996.
</P>
<P>
A report of the International Monetary Fund (IMF) obtained here
Friday attributed the increase to a sharp rise in the country's
oil production.
</P>
<P>
As a member of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting
Countries, Qatar was allocated an oil output quota of 378,000
barrels per day.
</P>
<P>
But the IMF estimated Qatar's real oil production at 590,000
barrels per day in 1997. The rise in oil production, together with
last year's high oil prices which averaged 19.03 dollars a barrel,
earned the country an extra 1.3 billion dollars in revenue.
</P>
