<HEADLINE> Six Whales Stranded off Northern German Coast, 3 Died </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Six sperm whales which lost their
way in the Atlantic ran aground Friday off the coast of the
northern German Eiderstedt Peninsula, three of them died several
hours later, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Another three whales were still seen alive in the flat waters
near the peninsula. Latest reports said there was a slim hope for
them to free themselves over the night.
</P>
<P>
The whales have a length of between 12 to 15 meters each and a
weight of about 20 tons.
</P>
<P>
In December, another 13 whales also went aground and died off
the Danish Rom Island.
</P>
<P>
According to estimates of marine biologists, the whale might
have gone astray due to disturbed magnetic field or unnatural
acoustic diversions. 
</P>
