<HEADLINE> Lebanese Muslims Celebrate Jerusalem Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of Lebanese Muslims
across the country Friday turned out for rallies to celebrate the
annual Jerusalem Day, the official National News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The day, which falls on the last Friday of Muslim's fasting
season of Ramadan each year, was initiated by late Iranian
spiritual leader Ayatollah Khomeini to voice support for the
Palestinian struggle against Israeli occupation of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Jerusalem, a city holy to Christians, Jews and Muslems, is at
the center of disputes between Israel and the Arabs.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Hassan Nasrallah, general secretary of the
Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, warned at a mass rally
in Beirut's southern suburbs that Israel is attempting to build a
big Jerusalem and judaize it.
</P>
<P>
"Israelis have been working on judaization of Jerusalem since
the first day when it was invaded by them. Over the past two
years, or since the conclusion of the Oslo accord, Israelis have
seized 36,500 square meters around the holy city in an attempt to
build a big Jerusalem," he said.
</P>
<P>
He accused Israel of trying to separate and isolate the city
from all Palestinian cities in the West Bank from the north to the
south and intensify efforts to build Jewish settlements.
</P>
<P>
Saying the reason for that is the halt of Palestinian's
rebellion, he criticized Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat for
"surrendering to the Israelis."
</P>
<P>
The Hezbollah is spearheading a guerilla war against the
Israeli occupation troops and trying to oust them from south
Lebanon. It has always been against any peace-making with Israel.
</P>
<P>
Besides Beirut, Muslims in Lebanon's other cities, such as
southern port city of Tyre and eastern area Belbek, also took part
in the celebrations. 
</P>
