<HEADLINE> Brazil to Face France in Beach Soccer Championships Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions
Brazil now have only France standing between them and a fifth
straight beach soccer world title as the two countries vies for
the gold medal here Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
Brazil have won all the previous tournaments and are the
odds-on favorite to triumph again.
</P>
<P>
The home side hammered three-time finalists Uruguay 5-1 while
France edged the tournament's sensation Peru 6-5 in a penalty
shoot-out at the semi-finals of the Annual Beach Soccer World
Championships on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Peru caused a major upset in the group competitions as they
killed off traditional favorites Argentina and Italy to make to
the last four alongside Brazil.
</P>
<P>
They will play Uruguay in the third-place playoff on Sunday.
</P>
