<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Red Cross Societies Donate More Money, Goods to Quake-Hit Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The Red Cross Society of China
has received donations worth more than 35.2 million yuan from
across China and the world for Zhangjiakou, which was hit a
6.2 earthquake 6.2 on the Richter Scale on Jan. 10.
</P>
<P>
The society has received 1.0051 million Swiss francs from Red
Cross and Red Crescent societies around the world, 75,000 Deutsch
marks from the German embassy, 50,000 Canadian dollars from the
Canadian embassy, and woollen blankets worth more than 410,000
yuan from the Japanese Red Cross Society.
</P>
<P>
Red cross societies in China have collected 13.04 million yuan
worth of money and articles for the quake-hit area which is more
than 200 kilometers northwest of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Red Cross Society has sent representatives to
Zhangbei to help with disaster relief, and the first relief fund
worth 11.14 million Hong Kong dollars has been put into use.
</P>
<P>
In another development, Baoshan Iron and Steel Complex, China's
largest steel producer, today donated 500,000 yuan to the
quake-hit area.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake killed about 50 people, injured more than 10,000
and damaged more than 100,000 houses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
