<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait Suspends Imports of Chicken From Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait declared Saturday
that it temporarily suspended imports of all species of birds and
chicken from Hong Kong and other parts of China.
</P>
<P>
Doctor Sultan Al-Khalaf, deputy director general of the
Livestock Affairs Department of the Kuwaiti Public Authority for
Agricultural and Fisheries Affairs was quoted by Kuwait News
Agency as saying that the measure was taken after the World
Health Organization confirmed existence of the birds flu disease
in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said the suspension of the imports was necessary to prevent
possible spread of the disease.
</P>
<P>
But he confirmed that the measure was precautionary because no
cases of the flu have been registered in the Gulf country.
</P>
<P>
The virus, not known to affect humans until 1997, has killed
six people in Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
