<DOCNO> XIE19980124.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Spokesman on Sino-Vietnamese Border Dispute </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokesman Zhu Bangzao today clarified the border dispute between
China and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese side has taken note of the remarks made on
Jan. 19 by a spokesman for Vietnam's Foreign Ministry and a
leading official of Quang Ninh Province of Vietnam concerning the
land border dispute.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese side built a herringbone dam on a boundary river
in Dongzhong section in the disputed area between the two
countries and raised and reinforced the dam since last August to
artificially change the alignment of the boundary river, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
In addition to jeopardizing Chinese interests, Zhu said, China
had to build a retaining wall to protect cultivated land and avoid
soil erosion.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese have taken into consideration the interests of
Vietnam in building the project, a sloping dam to release
floodwaters, he said.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that, although the Vietnamese side
unreasonably obstructed and disrupted the normal construction of
the project, China has always exercised restraint and tried to
seek a proper settlement to the issue through friendly
consultations.
</P>
<P>
Regrettably, Zhu said, the Vietnamese spokesman and the leading
official of the province made unwarranted reproaches of the
Chinese side and tried to mold public opinion by publicizing and
complicating the border dispute.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese view is that the Sino-Vietnamese border is tranquil
in general, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that any problems emerging on the long land
border between the two countries can be properly resolved through
existing channels as long as the two sides proceed from
Sino-Vietnamese traditional friendship and observe the spirit of
seeking truth from the facts and friendly consultations.
</P>
<P>
China will, as always, make unremitting efforts to this end,
Zhu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
