<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, Janurary 24 (Xinhua) -- Speed skating phenomenon
Catriona Le May Doan of Canada set a track record to win the first
run of women's 500 meters at the sprint world championships on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
World Cup leader and world record holder Le May Doan triumphed
with a record time of 38.60 seconds while the crowd favorite
Sandra Voelker of Germany was a distant second in 39.01 seconds
and Japan's Kyoko Shimazaki came third in 39.19.
</P>
<P>
The first run of the men's 500 meters went to Dutchman Jan Bos
with a track record of 36.03 seconds. Japanese Hiroyashu Shimizu
and World Cup leader Jeremy Wotherspoon of Canada shared second
place with the same time of 36.16.
</P>
<P>
Victory in the two-day competition goes to the skater with the
best combined results after two runs of both the 500 and the 1000
meters. 
