<HEADLINE> Ghedina Wins Italia's First Title on Streif piste </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, Janurary 24 (Xinhua) -- Kristian Ghedina on Saturday
became the first Italian downhiller to record a World Cup win at
Kitzbuehel, Austria.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old tamed the notorious piste in two minutes 5.49
seconds with second place going to Switzerland's Didier Cuche in
2:05.63.
</P>
<P>
Local favorite Josef Strobl came third in 2:05.85. 
</P>
</TEXT>
