</P>
<P>
-- President Clinton and his senior national security advisers
have concluded that a military strike against Iraq is likely
within a few weeks unless Iraqi President Saddam Hussein stops
interfering with the work of U.N. weapons inspectors, according to
highly placed U.S. officials.
</P>
