The New York Times:
</P>
<P>
-- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat left Washington considering
new American compromises but rejecting as "peanuts" Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu's offer of a limited Israeli redeployment from
less than 10 percent of the West Bank. But senior officials from
all sides said the gaps between the Israelis and the Palestinians
were narrowing. 
