<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French President Calls for Rapprochement with India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Visiting French President
Jacques Chirac Saturday said that France has called for a
rapprochement with Asia and India in particular.
</P>
<P>
Chirac arrived in Mumbai (Bombay), the biggest commercial city
in India, Saturday by a special aircraft from Paris to start his
three-day state visit to India.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a seminar of around 400 businessmen in Mumbai,
Chirac said, France "wants to establish a new, more ambitious
broader economic relationship with India." he said, adding
France's entrepreneurs "want to be your special partners in the
great European market."
</P>
<P>
"Let us be ambitious for our relationship...... Our economic
partnership must be worthy of a relationship established in
political and cultural fields," he further said.
</P>
<P>
Chirac is the first French head of state to visit India since
1989.
</P>
<P>
His trip will focus mainly on France's economic ties with
India. Two commercial contracts were signed at the start of
Chirac's visit. French firm Total is to invest around 300 million
dollars to help build a natural gas terminal in Bombay while
French bank Credit Commercial de France is to help fund an
infrastructure project in the southern state of Tamil Nadu.
</P>
</TEXT>
