<DOCNO> XIE19980124.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People Urged To Be Alert Against Fire During Holiday Period </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Public Security
issued an emergency circular here today cautioning people to be
alert against fire during the Spring Festival holiday beginning
Jan. 28.
</P>
<P>
The circular said there were 16 big fires across the country in
the last two months causing 122 deaths and injuring 55 people. The
economic loss was 28.66 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Spring Festival is usually a high-risk time for fires because
of the increased use of electricity and gas as well as
firecrackers and fireworks set off in holiday celebrations.
</P>
<P>
The circular asked fire-fighting departments to conduct
thorough checks in public places such as hotels, restaurants,
department stores and dance halls to reduce potential fire
danger. In large gatherings such as lantern shows,
fire-extinguishing facilities and equipment should be in place and
ready for use, the circular stated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
