<HEADLINE> Pakistan PM Expresses Grief at Loss of Lives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif has expressed his deep sense of grief over the tragic
road accident occurred Friday afternoon in Punjab province which
killed 24 people and injured 50 others.
</P>
<P>
Sharif also expressed sympathies with the families of the
victims and prayed for early recovery of the injured, according to
the Associated Press of Pakistan Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The report said, the accident took place Friday afternoon near
Narowal, about 120 kilometers southeast of Islamabad.
</P>
<P>
A coaster and a wagon were racing to take over each other when
they collided with a passenger bus coming from the opposite
direction, the report said.  
</P>
