<DOCNO> XIE19980124.0089 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Gold Reserves Found in Central China's Hunan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese geological workers
have discovered 41 tons of gold reserves in the western areas of
central China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
The geological team, headed by Professor He Jishan with
Zhongnan Engineering University, found the reserves in the deep
strata and neighboring areas of the Western Hunan Gold Mine. He is
also an academician of China Engineering Academy.
</P>
<P>
The team has also found 150,000 tons of fine antimony and 6,000
tons of tungsten trioxide. The new findings are estimated to have
a total value in excess of six billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Western Hunan Gold Mine is the largest gold production base in
south China. The new findings will help prolong the life of the
existing gold mine by 30 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
