<HEADLINE> Nagano to Welcome Record Number of Athletes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Host city Nagano will welcome a
record 2,450 athletes from a record 72 countries and regions to
February's Winter Olympics, organizers said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The United States will send the most athletes of 207, followed
by hosts Japan with 166 and Switzerland with 163 to the largest
Winter Games ever.
</P>
<P>
Kenya will make their Winter Games debut and plans to send two
athletes while Bermuda, Brazil, Iran, Luxembourg and Uruguay plan
to send only one athlete each.
</P>
<P>
The Nagano Games will see the number of women athletes jumping
by 52 percent compared with that of Lillehammer Games four years
ago.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 857 women will take part in the Games, up from 562
in Lillehammer.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,280 officials and coaches were also expected at the
Games, which run from February 7 to 22. 
</P>
</TEXT>
