<HEADLINE> French Foreign Minister Pays Informal Visit to HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 24 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister
Hubert Vedrine stopped over in Hong Kong Saturday following his
two-day official visit to Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Before leaving Hong Kong for India to join French President
Jacques Chirac, who is on a visit there, Vedrine told reporters at
the airport that he felt everything is going well in Hong Kong
after it returned to China in July last year.
</P>
<P>
Vedrine said that he had a meeting with Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa Saturday
 morning.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, they mainly discussed the current economic
and financial situation in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Tung explained to him some structural features that will enable
Hong Kong to overcome the financial turmoil in Asia, Vedrine said.
</P>
<P>
Over lunch, Vedrine met with Donald Tsang, financial secretary
of the SAR, and other business people.
</P>
<P>
Tsang told Vedrine that he was convinced that Hong Kong's
economy is strong and steady.
</P>
<P>
Vedrine arrived in Beijing on Thursday morning for a two-day
official visit to pave the way for a trip by French Prime Minister
 Lionel Jospin later this year.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Beijing, Vedrine met Chinese President Jiang
 Zemin, Vice Premier Li Lanqing and Vice Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen. 
</P>
