<HEADLINE> Democratic Party Chairman Issues New Year's Message </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- A senior official of a Chinese
democratic party called on overseas Chinese to continue concerning
themselves with China's development and to join people in the
motherland in their endeavor to build a better future.
</P>
<P>
Luo Haocai, chairman of the Zhi Gong Party (Public Interest
Party), made the call here today in his New Year's Message to
overseas Chinese, and people in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Luo extended his warmest new year's greetings and expressed
gratitude for their contributions to China's reform and opening-up
and modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
He reviewed what China achieved in the past year and pointed
out that Hong Kong has remained stable and prosperous and has a
high degree of autonomy as promised by the "one country, two
systems" formula as well as the HKSAR basic law.
</P>
<P>
"Macao will return to the motherland in 1999 and I believe the
Taiwan issue will be ultimately resolved," Luo
said. "Reunification is an irreversible historical trend."
</P>
<P>
He said the Zhi Gong Party will increase contact with overseas
Chinese in the new year, report to the central government opinions
and ideas of the overseas Chinese, and better protect their
interests.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1925, the China Zhi Gong Party was formed by
returned overseas Chinese, relatives of overseas Chinese, and
noted figures and scholars who have overseas ties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
