<HEADLINE> New Beginning For China's Relations With Britain, France (2) by Zhang Rongdian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Chirac said that new thinking and perspectives are
needed in French and Western European policies on China, and
that France will continue to promote a wide range of bilateral
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Hubert Vedrine, who is the first cabinet member of the new
French government to visit China, said on the eve of his visit
that France wishes to develop its relations with China and that
the Socialist government of Prime Minister Lionel Jospin attaches
as much importance to developing relations with China as does
Jacques Chirac.
</P>
<P>
China's Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen held
separate discussions with Cook and Vedrine on bilateral ties and
regional and international issues.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, in his meeting with Cook, expressed the belief that
Cook's China visit will help increase mutual understanding between
the two countries and bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Jiang told Vedrine that Sino-French relations are going
smoothly and have a promising future, and that China is willing to
work with France to further develop bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Local observers say that, with the increase in global
multi-polarization, increased dialogues and cooperation between
China and the two European nations will serve the long-term
interests of the three, increase cooperation between Asia and
Europe, and benefit world peace, stability and development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
