<HEADLINE> Rafter Upset by Berastegui in Australian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Patric Rafter of Australia was
upset Saturday by Alberto Berasategui in a thrilling third round
battle of men's singles at the Australian Tennis Open in
Melbourne, Australia.
</P>
<P>
The World No. 2 Australian wented down in 7-6, 6-7, 2-6 6-7.
</P>
<P>
Rafter was the highest ranking player toppled during the first
six days of the Australia Tennis Open following the defeat of
Michael Chang, Carlos Moya, Thomas Muster, Greg Rusedski, Iva
Majoli, Anna Kournikova and Irina Spirtea, Gustavo Kuerten, Goran
Ivanisevic and Mark Philippoussis. 
