<HEADLINE> Gold Price in Hong Kong Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The gold price in Hong Kong
rose 60 HK dollars Saturday to close at 2,753 HK dollars a tael,
according to Po Sang Bank, one of the major gold dealers in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gold price is equivalent to 298.43 U.S. dollars a troy
ounce, up 6.48 U.S. dollars from the previous close at Saturday's
exchange rate of one U.S. dollar to 7.7435 HK dollars. 
</P>
