<HEADLINE> World Children Art Exhibition to Open in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The "World Boys and Girls Art
 Exhibition," an education show at its grandest scale, will be
held in Hong Kong in February, with 161 countries or regions to
attend, a local culture department official confirmed Saturday.
</P>
<P>
With "Earth -- Our Wonderland" as its main theme, the
exhibition will provide an opportunity for children to express
their joys, sadness, realities, determinations, dreams, the
future, loved ones and their lives.
</P>
<P>
"The objectives of the exhibition is to promote international
understanding, peace and awareness of children's rights, and to
serve as a medium for children around the world to learn about one
another through their paintings," the official said.
</P>
<P>
Japan, France, Canada, Mongolia, Armenia, Georgia, Azerbaijan
and most recently Russia, have all held the exhibition. After
being held in Hong Kong on February 18-23, it will make its way
to South Africa.  
</P>
</TEXT>
