<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Polish Parliament Adopts 1998 Draft Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The lower house of the Polish
parliament on Friday adopted the 1998 draft budget after minor
changes.
</P>
<P>
The budget, proposed by the government led by Jerzy Buzek at
the end of 1997, was adopted by 254 votes for, 173 against and six
abstentions, reported the Polish Press Agency.
</P>
<P>
Under Poland's financial act, its 1998 expenditure will total
143.4 billion zlotys (40.97 billion U.S. dollars) and revenue
will total 129 billion zlotys (36.9 billion dollars), with a
deficit standing at 14.4 billion zlotys (4.1 billion dollars), or
2.8 percent of the gross domestic product (GDP).
</P>
<P>
The budget, based on the one made by the former government led
by Wlodzimierz Cimoszewicz, has lowered the GDP growth rate from
six percent to 5.6 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
