<HEADLINE> Export of Central Hunan Province Picks Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The export of central China's
Hunan province in 1997 rose again after a fall in the previous two
years.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the province's foreign trade volume over
the last year reached 1.89 billion U.S.dollars, with the export
trade volume of 1.44 billion U.S.dollars, increasing by 12 percent
compared with 1996.
</P>
<P>
The export of clothes, domestic animals, cement and zinc
increased by a big margin, while that of lead and shoes slightly
dropped over the same period of 1996, according to an official of
the provincial customs office.
</P>
<P>
The official said that Hunan's export volume to Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) in 1997 increased by 11 percent
to hit 280 million U.S.dollars, which also shows the growing
economic relation between Hong Kong and inland area.  
</P>
</TEXT>
