<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 64 More AIDS Cases Reported in Hong Kong Last Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Sixty-four AIDS cases were
reported in 1997 in Hong Kong, bringing the total number of AIDS
cases to 309, the Department of Health announced Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The department said that a total of 181 persons were found
positive for the HIV antibody test last year, bringing the
cumulative total number of reported HIV infections to 957.
</P>
<P>
This is the highest number of new HIV infections ever received
in a single year in Hong Kong since the surveillance system was
established in 1984.
</P>
<P>
The ratio of reported male to female infections is four to one.
Over 80 percent acquired the infection via sexual contact, the
department said.
</P>
<P>
Routes of transmission of the 957 HIV infected were: 506
through heterosexual and 284 through homosexual or bisexual; 16
were injecting drug users; four were mother-to-child transmission
around the time of birth; and 67 acquired the infection through
contaminated blood or blood products.
</P>
<P>
As for the remaining 80, the department said, the information
available was inadequate for classification. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
