<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asian Airlines Warn of Baggage Limits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Passengers are reminded by
airlines across Asia of strict limits on hand baggage in the
run-up to Lunar New Year, local newspapers reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Cathay Pacific Airways, the largest of the three international
airlines in Hong Kong, said it will only accept hand baggage which
fits into an area measuring 56 cm by 36 cm by 23 cm, and weighs
less than five kilograms.
</P>
<P>
The newspapers quoted Henry Mok, manager of the Cathay Pacific
Airports for customer services, as saying: "We are seeing a trend
towards passengers carrying more hand baggage and the airlines
need to introduce stringent controls and guidelines."
</P>
<P>
The trend "poses a direct safety risk to passengers and crew
members alike," said Richard Stirland, director-general of the
Association of Asia Pacific Airlines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
