<HEADLINE> Tung Visits PLA Hong Kong Garrison </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) Tung Chee Hwa visited
the Stanley Barracks Saturday to deliver his Spring Festival's
greetings to the People's Liberation Army (PLA) Garrison stationed
in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Tung was welcomed by the PLA Commander Liu Zhenwu and the
Political Commissar Xiong Ziren when he arrived at the barracks
Saturday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The Chief Executive toured the quarters and a culture
activities center, where soldiers spend their spare time for
reading, enjoying music, and doing exercises. Historic exhibits,
calligraphy works, paintings and light weapons are displayed at
the center.
</P>
<P>
Tung told the PLA officers and soldiers Saturday that they have
contributed to the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong since the
Garrison started to be responsible for the defense of Hong Kong on
July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The PLA Garrison has set up a very good image in Hong Kong and
is welcomed by the SAR government and the people, said Tung. He
noted that the troops have strictly observed military rules and
the Basic Law, the SAR's constitutional document.
</P>
<P>
He also took the opportunity to send greetings to the Garrison
as the traditional Chinese Lunar New Year, which falls on January
28 this year, is drawing near.
</P>
<P>
Commander Liu Zhenwu expressed his thanks to the SAR government
and the Hong Kong people for their kindness and support to the
army.
</P>
<P>
The Chief Executive was accompanied on the hour-long visit by
acting Secretary for Administration Michael Suen, Financial
Secretary Donald Tsang, Secretary for Justice Elsie Leung,
Secretary for Security Peter Lai, and Secretary for Home Affairs
David Lan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
