<HEADLINE> Earthquake-Hit Areas Receive Foreign Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Civil Affairs
announced here today that it has received donations for the
earthquake-stricken areas in Zhangjiakou of Hebei Province from
many foreign governments and organizations.
</P>
<P>
Zhangjiakou, a major city in northern Hebei, was hit on January
10 by a magnitude 6.2 tremor, which killed about 50 people,
injured over 10,000 and damaged more than 100,000 houses.
</P>
<P>
According to the civil affairs ministry, the latest foreign
donations to Zhangjiakou include 100,000 US dollars from the
Libyan government, 1,000 US dollars from the Sudanese Embassy in
Beijing, over 184,700 RMB yuan from the Beijing Japanese School,
Japanese Chamber of Commerce in China and Beijing Japanese
Society, and three million Japanese yen from the Toyota Company of
Japan. 
</P>
