<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Biography Of legendary Chinese Mathematician </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- A biography of Chen Jingrun, a
legendary Chinese mathematician who died in March of 1996, was
published recently in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Chen was an academic with the Chinese Academy of Sciences, who
published his work on Goldbach's conjecture, which greatly
advanced a proof, in 1973, and a theorem has been named after him.
</P>
<P>
Despite having to live and work in quite harsh conditions
during the Cultural Revolution, Chen managed to complete his thesis
which shocked the scientific community, and he was considered an
model inspiration for the Chinese youth.
</P>
<P>
The biography was written with the help of Chen's secretary,
news reporters, colleagues and relatives.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
