<HEADLINE> Leading Guangdong Insurer Offers Huge Property Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 24 (Xinhua) -- A leading property insurer of
Guangdong Province underwrote policies worth over 1,700 billion
yuan (205 billion US dollars) for both domestic and overseas
clients in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The Guangdong Property Insurance Company under the People's
Insurance Company of China Group dealt with over 200,000 claims
and offered compensations valued at 2.95 billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
There were a dozen big compensation cases including over 20
million yuan for losses caused by typhoon and over 30 million yuan
for flood damages.
</P>
<P>
The company also cooperated with meteorological and other
departments to help the insured in prevention of calamities,
thus reducing an estimated 10 billion yuan of losses.
</P>
<P>
Due to business readjustment, insurance policies concerning
enterprise property, cargo transport, farming, export credit,
aviation and space development saw sharp increases last
year. 
</P>
