<HEADLINE> Traditional Chinese Medicine Being Used To Treat Difficult Diseases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Traditional Chinese medicine
doctors in the northern city of Tianjin have found a
way to treat gangrene in a diabetic's foot.
</P>
<P>
Gangrene is one of the serious complications of diabetes, and
often accompanies hepatic and renal dysfunction and other
problems.
</P>
<P>
The hospital's Doctor Yang Zhaogang has also used long needles
and acupuncture to cure prostate disease, which has been effective
in 89 percent of the cases.
</P>
<P>
Western and traditional Chinese medicines were both thought to
be unable to cure the disease, but Yang has been using the therapy
since the '60s, and has been praised by Chinese experts. The long
needle can reach specific acupuncture points deep below the skin.
</P>
</TEXT>
