<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 13,500 Vietnamese Workers to Leave South Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Some 13,500 Vietnamese workers
have to leave South Korea as the financial crisis in this Asian
country deepens, according to a report reaching here saturday.
</P>
<P>
the Vietnamese Embassy in Seoul said the number of Vietnamese
workers in South Korea will drop considerably betwenn now and the
year 2000 due to an economic slowdown, official press in Ho Chi
Minh city reported.
</P>
<P>
So far this month, around 1,000 Vietnamese workers have
returned home. Last year, domestic employment service companies
did not sign any contracts to export labor to South Korea.
</P>
<P>
There are currently 220,000 guest-workers in South Korea
including some 20,000 Vietnamese who are chiefly employed by small
South Korean enterprises in such labor-intensive sectors as
textiles and construction.
</P>
<P>
in 1998, Vietnam is expected to send workers to new foreign
markets such as Japan, the US and the Middle East, accrding to the
report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
