<HEADLINE> Fruit Fly Discovered In Guangzhou Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Quarantine officials in
Guangzhou, the capital of China's Guangdong Province, announced
today that an especially harmful species of fruit fly was found
earlier this month at the city's Baiyun International Airport.
</P>
<P>
On January 3, ten larvas of the fly, Bactrocera neohumeralis,
were found in a package of of chilis brought in by an Australian
passenger.
</P>
<P>
The larvas were hatched under laboratory conditions, and
Quarantine officers confirmed that they were indeed the
particular species and this was the first time that it has
been found here.
</P>
<P>
According to the Guangzhou Quarantine Animals and Plants
Bureau, the fly can affect almost all types of fruit and
vegetable. 
</P>
</TEXT>
