<DOCNO> XIE19980124.0130 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Seen as "Safe Island" in Asian Financial Crisis  (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In another analysis, China's foreign debt situation in general
is good, with all the major indices tracking the health of its
foreign debt level all well below internationally accepted
standards.
</P>
<P>
China's debt-servicing ratio, or the ratio of repayment of debt
principal and interest to foreign exchange income of the same
year, is 11.8 percent, compared with the commonly recognized
standard of 20 percent. The debt ratio, which is the result of the
outstanding value of a country's foreign debt divided by its gross
domestic product, stands at 14 percent, far below the average for
developing nations.
</P>
<P>
Short-term debt accounts for just 12 percent of China's total
foreign debt, valued at 118.6 billion US dollars at the end of
last June.
</P>
<P>
Last year China took a series of measures to open wider to the
outside world and stimulate domestic consumption, such as lowering
interest rates and the general level of tariff duties and allowing
some foreign trade companies to open foreign-exchange accounts.
</P>
<P>
Bao said that these measures, taken under the backdrop of
financial instability in many other parts of Asia, indicate that
the Chinese government is confident of its economic prowess and
international payment ability.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, these measures will also play a positive role in
eventually cooling the Asian financial crisis, restoring the
international economic order and boosting global economic growth,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Pieter Bottelier, a senior advisor to the World Bank's vice
president for East Asia and Pacific Region, said here earlier this
month that China is a stabilizer in the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
"China is an important positive factor in helping stabilize the
financial situation in Asia. Without it, the situation would have
been even worse," said Bottelier, former chief of the Bank's
resident mission in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
