<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- A snow storm hit hard on the southern part of
Romania Friday, closing down airports and cutting off power supply
to hundreds of towns and villages.
</P>
<P>
The storm dumped up to 190 centimeters of snow on the ground in
some areas of southern and central Romania, stranding drivers on
highways and interrupting train service. (Romania-Storm)
</P>
