<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Henan Boosts Agricultural Industrialization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Henan Province, one of
China's largest grain bases, will continue to devote major
efforts to agricultural industrialization in a bid to
transform the traditional farming into a modern industry.
</P>
<P>
Henan had more than 3,490 agricultural organizations by the end
of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Related organizations have signed contracts valued at 8.24
million yuan with 30 percent of Henan's rural households. Said
contracts cover supplies and purchases of major agricultural
products. The system enables farmers to remain aware of constantly
changing market conditions.
</P>
<P>
Related organizations formed numerous agronomic, wholesale and
cultivation ventures which have provided farmers with technical
guidance and market information.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural industrialization departments in Henan have a
combined fixed asset value of 13.4 billion yuan, with their total
1997 output value standing at 53.3 billion yuan last year. The per
capita annual income for farming households jumped by 87 yuan in
1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
