<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Establish Consumer Protection Authority </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
decided to set up a consumer protection authority, Internal and
External Trade Minister Kingsley T. Wickramaratne said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the Department of Internal Trade, the Fair
Trading Commission and the Public Enterprises Reform Commission
will be merged into one authority in a bid to strengthen consumer
protection efforts.
</P>
<P>
The authority will monitor the quality of imported goods to
ensure low-quality products will not flood into Sri Lanka,
according to the minister.
</P>
<P>
He did not mention when the authority will be set up. 
</P>
