<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique's Cotton Production Increases by 40% </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique's cotton production
in the 1996/97 season is estimated at 74,000 tons, a 40 percent
increase over the scheducled target of 53,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The mozambique Cotton Association said in a statement Friday
that the association has purchased 72,300 tons of cotton by
Juanary 14, local newspaper Noticias reported today.
</P>
<P>
At the 1996/97 season, 153,000 hectares of cotton was planted
in the country.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique is one of the major cotton exporters in Africa.
During the 1996/97 season which ends in March, the country has
exported 10,886 tons of ginned cotton, earning the country 16,1
million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
But the association said that the ailing cotton market has
cast a shadow on Mozambique's cotton export as the cotton price
has downed from the 1,600 U.S. Dollars a ton in June last year to
1,400 dollars at present. 
</P>
</TEXT>
