<HEADLINE> Guangzhou-Shenzhen Railway Resumes Traffic After Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The Guangzhou-Shenzhen
Railway, on which a train collision occurred Thursday, in south
China resumed operation this morning.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,000 railway workers and over 100 soldiers of the
People's Liberation Army cleared the wreckage in less than 20
hours.
</P>
<P>
Mudflows collapsed a section of a wall along the railway
Thursday evening and caused the derailment of a locomotive.
</P>
<P>
A short time later, an empty passenger train collided with the
overturned locomotive, killing one engineer and wounding five
railway workers.
</P>
<P>
</P>
