<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hebei Unveils Blueprint for Urban Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province in north
China projects that some eight million rural people will migrate
to local urban districts by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Hebei's urban population is expected to hit 25 million people,
or 33 percent of its total population.
</P>
<P>
The aforementioned projections are contained in the provincial
plan for urban development through the year 2010, which was
recently approved by the Standing Committee of the Provincial
People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Two new cities with a population of 500,000 people each will be
established in the ports of Jingtang and Huanghua now under
construction.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-Tianjin Plateau and areas around the provincial
capital of Shijiazhuang will have a dense urban population by the
year 2000. Over 50 percent of Hebei's total population will live
in urban areas by the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 130 counties and 33 cities. Some 70
percent of its counties will become small or medium-sized cities
by the year 2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
