<HEADLINE> Traffic Accident in Tanzania Kills 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed
and three others were injured after a pick-up overturned at Wami
in the Coast Region, Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
According to police and hospital reports, the driver and five
passengers died instantly, while the seventh died at the
hospital.
</P>
<P>
The vehicle was heading to Lushoto from Dar es Salaam
Wednesday when it overturned at 1 am. The bodies were not
collected until 16 hours after the incident due to transport
problems, press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The police are still investigating the cause of the incident.
</P>
<P>
This is a second fatal traffic accident in 10 days, despite
the fact that the country has vowed to get tough on reckless
drivers. On January 16, a traffic accident caused by overspeeding
left 25 people dead and 46 others injured in the Coast Region.
</P>
