<HEADLINE> Autumn Grain Purchases In Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province has purchased 2.3 billion kg of autumn grain from local
farmers, sources have reported, even though the province was
hit by severe drought last year, resulting in decreased output.
</P>
<P>
To keep farmers enthusiastic and to help increase their income,
the provincial government has adopted price protection measures in
accordance with the province's conditions.
</P>
<P>
The province's Agriculture Development Bank branch has prepared
4.7 billion yuan for autumn grain purchases, and local governments
have increased supervision of grain purchases. Various areas have
tried to see to it that there is adequate capital for grain
purchase, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning farmers had a rise of 300 yuan in their income last
year despite the drought. This has been attributed to the
province's increased investment in agriculture and concentration
on cereals, aquatic products, cash crops, and livestock. 
</P>
</TEXT>
