<HEADLINE> China's Largest Container Shipping Co. Established in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 24 (Xinhua) -- China's largest container
shipping company was established here on Friday after COSCO
Container Lines (COSCON) merged with the Shanghai Ocean Shipping
Co.
</P>
<P>
The new company, COSCO Container Shipping Co. Ltd., will also
merge container shipping companies of the China Ocean Shipping
Company (COSCO) in Guangzhou and Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
An official from COSCON pointed out that it is extremely
important for China to pace with developments in the container
shipping sector and continue the process of building Shanghai into
an international shipping center.
</P>
<P>
The business scope of the new company, which is registered in
the Pudong New Area, ranges from container shipping and ship
leasing to marketing and related businesses.
</P>
<P>
The company plans to open branches in the United States, Europe
and the Asian-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
It also plans to invest in a container berth at
Shanghai Port and further increase cooperation with coastal
firms and the many shipping firms operating along the Yangtze
River.
</P>
<P>
The fifth largest container shipping company in the world,
COSCON had total assets of 23 billion yuan. With 151 ships, it
handled 3.25 million TEU of containers in 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
