<HEADLINE> Nagano Olympic Village Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The Nagano Olympic Village opened
Saturday two weeks before the central Japanese city hosts the
Winter Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
"Preparations for welcoming athletes and officials as our
family members have been made," village mayor Shozo Sasahara said
at the opening ceremony as snow fell.
</P>
<P>
The village is located seven kilometers south of central Nagano
and will be home to some 3,000 competitors and officials during
the 16-day Games opening on February 7.
</P>
<P>
The Nagano Olympics will be the biggest Winter Games yet with
more than 70 countries and regions expected to participate,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
Several delegation officials from Japan, Britain and the United
States checked into the village after the ceremony, officials
said, with dozens of other Olympic officials and athletes from
Canada, Italy, Poland and Chinese Taipei scheduled to arrive here
late Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Main Press Center and the International Broadcasting Center
(IBC), both located several kilometers east of the athletes'
village, also opened on Saturday. 
</P>
