<HEADLINE> Hebei to Open Additional Commodity Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 24 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province plans to invest 3.8 billion yuan this year in building
50-odd commodity markets during 1998, up 11 percent on 1997.
</P>
<P>
The province's 4,750 markets of all kinds will have a total
annual turnover of 150 billion yuan, with some 25 markets
expected to record turnover in excess of one billion yuan each.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the province will establish 100-plus markets
directly related to production, including 10 labor, 25 technician
exchange, 10 technology markets and five information services
markets.
</P>
<P>
Projections call for the province to have a total of 10,600
related markets by the end of this year, including 1,715 labor
markets, 4,675 technology markets and 3,535 information service
markets.
</P>
<P>
Investments in the construction of commodity markets will hit
1.7 billion yuan during the year, 45 percent of Hebei's total
investment.  
</P>
