<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- World No.5 Greg Rusedski of
Britain was beaten 6-7, 4-6, 2-6 today by Australian Todd
Woodbridge at the Australian Tennis Open in Melbourne, Australia.
</P>
<P>
Rusedski and Anna Kournikova were so far the only two seeds
players defeated today during third rounds of men's and women's
singles.
</P>
<P>
Tope seed Martina Hingis, 17, defeated Kournikova 6-4, 4-6,
6-4.
</P>
<P>
Seeds Amanda Coetzer (3), Mary Pierce (5), Arantxa Sanchez
Vicario (7) Anke Huber (10) and Dominique Van Roost (14) all made
it safely through to the fourth round.
</P>
<P>
Coetzer defeated the sole remaining Australian woman, Annabel
Ellwood, from Australia, 6-3, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
It was an easier encounter for the tiny South African than
their only other meeting, in the Federation Cup last year when she
won in three sets.
</P>
<P>
Pierce, whose win in Melbourne in 1995 remains her only grand
slam success, had a little more trouble with the blonde from
Minsk, Belarus, Olga Barabanschikova before edging past her 7-5,
6-3.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez Vicario, who bounced back to win in Sydney last week
after a year without a title, overpowered Japan's Rika Hiraki 6-2,
6-3.
</P>
<P>
Dominique Van Roost of Belgium defeated Yayuk Basuki of
Indonesia 6-4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Anke Huber of Germany beat Joannette Kruger of South Africa 6-7
(7-4), 6-3, 6-2 in the women's singles. 
