<HEADLINE> S. Lanka Takes Steps to Ease Teacher Shortage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
decided to appoint 1,031 teachers next Monday to ease the shortage
in the north and east, officials said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Of the new teachers, 916 are Tamils and the rest Sinhalese.
They all had passed interviews held last September and December.
</P>
<P>
They will be given three weeks of introductory training
starting next Tuesday before being assigned to schools in the
north and east, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, about 934 Tamils and 118 Sinhalese people will
be interviewed this month at the offices of Education Directors in
their respective districts.
</P>
<P>
Those who pass the interviews will also be appointed as
teachers before the 50th anniversary of the country's Independence
Day, which falls on February 4.  
</P>
