<HEADLINE> Weekly Report on Kuala Lumpur Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) ended the week mixed.
</P>
<P>
Over the week, the Composite Index lost 18.60 points to 558.57,
the Emas Index added 3.38 points to 140.57 and the Industrial
Index jumped 69.48 points to 1,152.13.
</P>
<P>
On the main board, volume increased to 1.308 billion stocks
valued at 3.135 billion ringgit (about 697 million U.S. dollars)
from 1.036 billion shares worth 2.236 billion ringgit (about 497
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover rose to 281.014 million shares worth
646.788 million ringgit (about 143.73 million U.S. dollars) from
170.683 million stocks valued at 312.254 million ringgit (about
69.39 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals improved to 65.894 million stocks valued at
232.818 million ringgit (about 51.74 million U.S. dollars) from
47.910 million shares worth 164.092 million ringgit (about 36.46
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The top 10 active counters during the week were United
Engineers, adding 16 sen to 2.09 ringgit; Sime Darby, gaining 34
sen to 4.54 ringgit; Ekran, falling 1.93 ringgit to 82.5 sen;
Tenaga Nasional, up 25 sen to 6.80 ringgit; Renong, dipping one
sen to 73 sen; Granite, down 73 sen to 55 sen; Intria, perking one
sen to 36.5 sen; Time Engineering, gaining 10 sen to 60 sen; MBf
Capital, up five sen to 97 sen and MBf Land, up seven sen to 35.5
sen.
</P>
<P>
Consumer products accounted for 68.433 million shares traded,
industrial product 106.307 million, construction 202.606 million,
trading/services 367.084 million, infrastructure 5.524 million,
finance 188.959 million, hotels 5.399 million, properties 182.920
million, plantations 57.904 million, mining 24.970 million, trusts
1.156 million, closed-end fund 1.799 million, loan stocks 89.884
million and rights 4.535 million.  
</P>
