<HEADLINE> Hingis Beats Kournikova in Australian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Martina Hingis of Switzerland
made a narrow win over Anna Kournikova of Russia today at 1998
Australian Tennis Open in Melbourne, Australia.
</P>
<P>
Kournikova may be the pin-up girl of women's tennis but Hingis
remains the world No. 1 although it nearly ended today.
</P>
<P>
The two teenagers staged a thrilling third round clash before a
packed center court with Hingis eventually prevailing 6-4, 4-6, 6-4
after just over an hour and a half.
</P>
<P>
While the victory keeps the world No.1 on course for a second
successive Australian Open crown, the match showed that the gap
between the 17-year-old Swiss and the host of challengers for her
crown is narrowing.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time 16-year-old Kournikova had taken a set
off Hingis and at times the Russian rattled her with her power
from the back court.
</P>
<P>
In their two previous meetings Kournikova had been thrashed by
Hingis, losing 6-3, 6-2 in last year's Wimbledon semi-finals and
before that 6-1, 6-3 in the third round of the French Open.
</P>
<P>
Kournikova made 53 unforced errors in all in today's game,
nearly double Hingis' total of 27 but could be happy in the
knowledge that Hingis at least had to work up a sweat to beat her
this time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
