<HEADLINE> 10 Killed in Bangladesh Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were killed
and 40 others injured when a passenger bus collided with a
speeding truck on the Dhaka-Chittagong highway early Thursday
morning, the local press reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred near Cormila, some 90 km southeast of the
capital city. The bus then fell into a roadside ditch, killing
seven people on the spot.
</P>
<P>
Three others, including a serviceman, died later, police said.
</P>
<P>
Most of the injured were rushed to hospital. A case was lodged
with police, but no arrest had been made as both drivers of the
bus and the truck fled the scene after the accident.  
</P>
