<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Idea of Digging Kra Isthmus Canal in Thailand Revived </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Officials and businessmen in
Ranong, south Thailand, have revived the proposal to dig a canal
at Kra Isthmus between the Andaman Sea and the Gulf of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Shipping through a canal between the two waters can save time
and costs, promote investment and boost tourism, according to a
Bangkok Post report Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The proposed 100-km-long project, about 500 km southwest of
Bangkok, will cost 500-600 billion baht (10-12 billion US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The project has been deliberated by parliament 11 times over
the past few decades, but no decision has been made to launch it,
because of the enormous cost.
</P>
<P>
The public and private sectors of Ranong have decided to
request the government to make a study of the canal plan.
</P>
</TEXT>
