<HEADLINE> Arsenal Explodes in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, January 23 (Xinhua) -- An arsenal northeast of
Albania's capital Tirana exploded Thursday, killing one, wounding
one and bringing about serious material losses.
</P>
<P>
The arsenal, a tunnel housing large amounts of ammunitions in
Burrel, caught fire at about 14:00 o'clock Thursday, triggering a
string of blasts, the Albanian news agency ATA quoted a defense
source as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian security department and fire forces attempted to
bring the situation under control but failed.
</P>
<P>
The explosion lasted into late night and the arsenal was blasted
away.
</P>
<P>
Local police and experts from the Albanian defense department
are now investigating the cause of the explosion. 
