<HEADLINE> Three Foreign Firms to Open Plants in Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, January 23 (Xinhua) -- President Jose Maria Figueres
said on Friday that three foreign firms will open plants in his
country. That could mean some 700 new jobs.
</P>
<P>
The three firms are Photocircuits, of New York, which
manufactures integrated circuit cards, and a subsidiary of Dover
Corporation, also of New York, and EMC Technology, which produces
electronic parts for satellites and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
Photocircuit will build a plant in a duty-free zone in San Jose.
</P>
<P>
Dek USA, a Dover Corporation subsidiary, will give technical
support to companies in the country that use its equipment.
</P>
<P>
EMC will start building a plant to produce electronic
components for telecommunications equipment.
</P>
<P>
Figueres has launched a vigorous campaign to attract
investments from high technology firms. The biggest success of the
campaign was a decision made last year by Intel -- the biggest
microchip manufacturer of the world -- to install a plant in the
country. 
</P>
