<HEADLINE> European Delegation Urges Albania to Complete Legislation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, January 23 (Xinhua) -- A seven-member European
delegation on Friday called on all parities concerned in Albania
to complete the legislation of the country's constitution within
this year.
</P>
<P>
Europe opposed any new general elections in Albania, the
delegation said in a statement released at a press conference
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, composed of members from the European
Parliament, the Organization for Security and Cooperation in
Europe and the Council of Europe, arrived in Albania Thursday for
a two-day visit aimed at observing preprations of Albania's
legislative work.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, the delegation said it accepted the legality
of the June 29 elections and the newly-elected Albanian
parliament. It called on the Albanian Democratic Party to respect
the election results.
</P>
<P>
The delegation also called for an ealier solution to the
conflict between the Albanian Constitutional Court and the
People's Assembly of Albania, adding that the independence of the
legislative body should be respected.
</P>
<P>
The Democratic Party proposed holding new parliamentary
elections and refused to participate in the drafting of a new
constitution.
</P>
<P>
The Constitutional Court, meanwhile, was embattled with the
People's Assembly because the court refused to heed the latter's
suggestions to change some of its judges.
</P>
<P>
The European delegation met the Albanian president, president
of the People's Assembly, Albanian prime minister and leaders of
other parties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
