<HEADLINE> Storm Paralyzes Southern Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, January 23 (Xinhua) -- A snow storm hit hard on the
southern part of Romania Friday, closing down airports and cutting
off power supply to hundreds of towns and villages.
</P>
<P>
The storm dumped up to 190 centimeters of snow on the ground in
some areas of southern and central Romania, stranding drivers on
highways and interrupting train service.
</P>
<P>
A father and a son stranded in their car on the highway were
almost killed by tail exhaust as they tried to get warm by keeping
the motor running.
</P>
<P>
The Otopeni International Airport here and airports in many
other cities were shut down. The nation's sea port in Constanta
was also closed because of waves as high as nine meters.
</P>
<P>
Weather forecast said snow storm would continue to sweep across
the country in the coming days. 
</P>
