<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Exports Fresh Milk for First Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The first ever consignment of
fresh milk to be exported by Sri Lanka is scheduled to be shipped
from Colombo to Male, capital of the Maldives, Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's national news agency Lankapuvath said Saturday that
700 packs of Rich Life fresh milk and 1990 packs of Cheers fruit
juice drinks will be loaded into a container at a factory in
Wadduwa, 30 kilometers south of Colombo.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time Sri Lanka exports milk products, it
said.
</P>
<P>
A firm in Bangladesh also ordered a consignment of Rich Life
chocolate flavored milk and Cheers juice drinks, which will be
delivered shortly. Both the Rich Life and Cheers are local brand
names.
</P>
<P>
A 200 milliliter pack of Rich Life milk is sold at 45 Rupees
(73 U.S. cents) on the local market, whereas the same amount of
imported milk costs 75 Rupees (1.21 dollars).  
</P>
