<HEADLINE> Veteran Deputy to People's Congress in Tibet (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- A 66-year-old woman, Gyain Kong,
who was re-elected as deputy to the People's Congress of Nedong
County in Tibet, for the ninth time, said she feels great pride,
and will speak on behalf of the people who elected her.
</P>
<P>
Gyain Kong, who is known for her intelligent proposals and her
willingness to represent the ordinary folk, said that a growing
number of deputies are ready to speak out on behalf of the people
and to air their views about the government. During her previous
term at the Eighth People's Congress, she submitted over 30
proposals, all of which were adopted by local government.
</P>
<P>
In the past, she was hired as a laborer by a landowner. Before
1951, she recalled, she got down on her knees to beg the man who
owned serfs for any little thing her family needed and was often
refused.
</P>
<P>
A day she will never forget is March 2, 1963 when the First
People's Congress of Nedong County was held, and all sorts of
people dressed in clothes reserved only for major festivals rushed
out to the streets and started dancing and drinking.
</P>
<P>
They surrounded the deputies, who had pieces of red cloth
pinned to their clothing, giving them Hadas and raising toasts to
them. This went on for three days and nights, as people celebrated
a festival of their own, she explained.
</P>
<P>
The first proposal Gyain Kong submitted concerned unreasonable
grain prices set by the relevant government departments, and
within two days, the problem was solved.
</P>
<P>
The Communist Party of China kept its word, and they became the
masters of their own destiny, one of the Tibetans who drank that
evening told Gyain Kong at her residence, in celebration of the
successful proposal.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980124.0187 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
