<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan
Province recently opened the Funiu Mountain Nature Reserve which
covers more than 560 sq km in Xixia, Nanzhao, Luanchuan, Songxian,
Lushan and Neixiang counties.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Henan Forestry Department cited the reserve
as the largest of its kind in north and central China.
</P>
