<P>
YANGON, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar leader Lt. Gen. Tin Oo
has stressed the need for boosting production and promoting
export, saying that capital should be directed towards the
productive sector, the New Light of Myanmar newspaper reported on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting on production and financial matters
Friday, Lt. Gen Tin Oo, second secretary of the Myanmar State
Peace and Development Council, also urged officials to supervise
monetary affairs with great care so as to avoid mistakes in the
current monetary crisis in Asia.
</P>
<P>
