<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uruguayan Foreign Debt Totals 2.67 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The Uruguayan net foreign
debt in the public sector amounted to 2.67 billion U.S. dollars by
October 1997, 93 million dollars more than in 1996, the Central
Bank of Uruguay said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The gross foreign debt of Uruguay reached 5.5 billion dollars
in the same period last year and its external assets (most of its
international reserves) rose to 2.86 billion dollars, the bank
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
