<HEADLINE> Albanian President to Visit Washington </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Albanian President Rexhep
Mejdani will pay an unofficial visit to the United States on
January 31, a presidential spokesman said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Mejdani is expected to stay in the United States for seven
days, with meetings with senior U.S. government officials and
congressional leaders high on his agenda.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian president will also meet United Nations
Secretary General Kofi Annan during his America tour at the
invitation of a U.S. senator.
</P>
<P>
Mejdani's entourage will include Minister of Justice Thimio
Kondi and chairman of the Socialist Party parliamentary group
Pandeli Majko, the Albanian Telegraphic Agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
