<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand to Launch Campaign to Save Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government will
encourage people to use less water in a three-month campaign aimed
at preparing the country for an expected severe drought this year.
</P>
<P>
The campaign, which is to begin in February, would help educate
people on how to use water sparingly in most practical ways, said
Pinit Charusombat, deputy interior minister overseeing the
Provincial Waterworks Authority (PWA), the local press reported on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Pinit hoped the campaign would reduce water consumption by over
50 percent.
</P>
<P>
This would minimize the impact of the expected water shortage
resulting from prolonged dry spells in many areas last year.
</P>
<P>
To ensure the success of the campaign, Pinit said he and PWA
officials would make house calls which aim to increase the
public's awareness about water conservation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980124.0217 </DOCNO>
