<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian Coffee Exports Set New Record in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Brazil, the world's
largest coffee producer and exporter, last year earned a record
2.750 billion U.S. dollars from export of the product, reports
said here.
</P>
<P>
The figure surpassed the previous record of 2.6 billion dollars
registered in 1984, data from the Brazilian Coffee Exporters
Association (Abecafe) showed.
</P>
<P>
The 1997 income rose by 60 percent from 1996's 1.7 billion
dollars, added Abecafe.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the country exported 14.5 million 60-kilo bags,
compared with 13 million in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Germany for the first time became the largest market of
Brazilian coffee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
