<HEADLINE> Colombia Seizes 149 Tons of Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Colombian antidrug
police have seized approximately 149 tons of cocaine and
marijuana, and 124 tons of chemicals to process cocaine in several
searching operations in the last 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
A laboratory to process cocaine was discovered and destroyed
near Santa Marta, and 720 kilograms of refined cocaine and cocaine
base, 128 tons of coca leaves, 215 tons of chemical products and
110,915 gallons of liquid substances to process cocaine were
seized, said police.
</P>
<P>
Near Buga in the Valle municipality, police discovered a truck
with 21 tons of baled marijuana and detained a person. Other 100
kilograms of cocaine were discovered in a cattle transport vehicle
near Florencia.
</P>
<P>
Antidrug police also said that 21 rustic laboratories for the
processing of cocaine were destroyed in a rural area of the
Valparaiso municipality, and 128 kilograms of cocaine base and
chemicals for processing drugs were also found. 
</P>
</TEXT>
