<HEADLINE> Soccer Star Ronaldo Fined in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Inter Milan's Ronaldo was fined
two million lira (1,150 U.S. dollars) for comments about referees
by Italian football's disciplinary committee on Friday, reports
reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian claimed that penalty decisions had been biased
against Inter in their game against Sampdoria on December 6, but
were biased in Juventus' favour in their match at home to Lazio
on the same day.
</P>
<P>
His club were also fined the same amount for the comments made
by Ronaldo.
</P>
<P>
Vittorio Cecchi Gori was meanwhile banned from exercising his
duties as president of Fiorentina for 30 days and his club fined
30 million lira (17,000 dollars) for comments he made about
referees and Italy's soccer authorities. 
