by Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi to Bulgaria on February 24,
1998.
</P>
<P>
Trade volume between Bulgaria and Italy amounted to 700-800
million U.S. dollars in 1994-1997, with Bulgaria running a
surplus. There are about 500 companies with Italian-held interest
in Bulgaria. 
