<HEADLINE> Commercial Housing Market Expanding in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 24 (Xinhua) -- More and more residents in east
China's Fujian Province have had their own houses since 1997.
</P>
<P>
The total floor space of commercial housing sold from January
to November last year hit one million square meters, up 14
percent over the same period of 1996, according to the provincial
statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Bureau officials said the individual demand for commercial
houses is expected to continue to rise this year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 10.2 billion yuan (1.27 billion
U.S. dollars) was invested last year in Fujian's real estate
market, up 9.3 percent over the same period of 1996. Of that
total, 9.5 billion yuan was poured into the construction of
commercial housing, an increase of 1.8 percent over 1996.
</P>
<P>
The stable growth of investment in the province's real estate
market may indicate the recovery of the industry, said sector
insiders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
