<HEADLINE> Guangxi Region of China to Increase Grain Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region, which had good grain harvests for three
consecutive years, plans to increase grain production by 400,000
tons in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The region reported 16.61 million tons of grain in 1997,
550,000 tons more than 1996, local sources said.
</P>
<P>
To achieve the goal, the regional government will give priority
to the application of 10 agricultural techniques, including hybrid
seed and plastic sheeting for maize growing.
</P>
<P>
The plan is encouraging, considering a predicted decline of
China's grain output in 1998, as agriculture has already faced
pressure arising from low prices for grain last year,
analysts said.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, China produced 492.5 million tons of grain, almost the
same amount of grain as it did in 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
