of compliance" with Security Council's demands imposed after the
1991 Gulf War, she said.
</P>
<P>
"As we have all said, we would prefer to have a diplomatic
solution. The president (Bill Clinton) made that clear. But we are
not ruling any options out," she said. "Again as the president
said, something is going to give in this situation sooner or
later." But Albright declined to give any deadline for that.
