London had confined its losses to about 25 points until the
opening bell in New York, but soon extended its fall as the Dow
was hit by a sell program.
</P>
<P>
Weakness in the March FTSE future also weighed on sentiment
here.
</P>
<P>
Oils lost ground after disappointing results from some of the
US oil giants, with British Petroleum and Shell falling 4.24 and
3.97 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The DAX-30 index in Frankfurt closed floor trading at 4,237.31,
up 17.06 points. But volumes were thin as investors seemed loath
to commit ahead of the weekend, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
In later screen-based trade the IBIS DAX index ended down 16.61
points at 4,222.16.
</P>
<P>
French shares in Paris finished the session 22.44 points lower
at 2,966.15, a fall of 9.94 from last week, as share prices were
depressed by the weaker dollar and profit-taking at the end of the
monthly account. 
</P>
</TEXT>
