<HEADLINE> ILO: Uganda to Host African Tripartite Meeting on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The Ugandan government is to
host an international conference on child labor in Africa early
next month, the Geneva-based International Labor Organization
(ILO) announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Delegations, representing governments, employer's and worker's
organizations from 22 African countries will meet in Kampala,
Uganda, on February 5-7.
</P>
<P>
The African Tripartite Meeting on Child Labor is being
organized by the Organization of African Unity (OAU) with the
ILO's active support.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will provide an important venue for information,
discussion and debate on the extent of child labor in Africa and
possible national and international initiatives to address this
growing problem, according to the ILO.
</P>
<P>
The ILO has prepared a report for the conference, which will be
made public one day before the meeting begins. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
