<DOCNO> XIE19980124.0255 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece Decides to Scrap Article 19 of Citizenship Code </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The Greek cabinet decided today
to abolish article 19 of the citizenship code enabling the state
to strip members of ethnic minorities of their citizenship when
they leave the country with the intention of not returning.
</P>
<P>
Greek government spokesman Dimitris Reppas said that a draft
law would soon be tabled in Greece's parliament approving the
cabinet's decision.
</P>
<P>
The provision, he said, had in fact become inoperative because
only 70 persons lost last year their Greek citizenship in
accordance with the provision.
</P>
<P>
The article had come into force by virtue of a legislative
decree in 1955, and 60,000 people had since lost their Greek
citizenship.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Greece's Interior, Public Administration and
Decentralization Minister Alekos Papadopoulos said today that
article 20 of the same code which enables the state to strip
persons of their citizenship for espionage would remain in force.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
