<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Second Indiana Nurse Charged with Killing Patients </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 23 (Xinhua) -- An Indiana nurse was
arrested Thursday on charges of giving deadly injections to
patients, the United Press International said in a report today.
</P>
<P>
Cheryl May, 32, was arrested as a result of investigations on
dozens of deaths at three nursing homes in Fort Wayne County where
May worked.
</P>
<P>
The report said that a nurse who worked with May told police
she once suggested a deadly injection for a whining patient.
Police have confiscated a bottle of a morphine-containing drug
Roxanol from the nursing station where May worked at Courtland
Health and Rehabilitation Center.
</P>
<P>
Last month a former licensed practical nurse was arrested on
similar but unrelated charges for six deaths at a hospital in
Clinton, Indiana.
</P>
<P>
Reports quoted authorities as saying that Orville Lynn Majors
Jr. may have given lethal injections to as many as 165 patients
over a 22-month period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
